---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About | Jun Clemente"
  description="About Jun Clemente — applied data scientist based in San Diego, CA."
>
  <main class="mw8 center ph3 ph4-ns pv5" style="padding-top: 7rem;">
    <header class="mb4 mb5-ns">
      <h1 class="f2 f1-ns fw6 ma0">About</h1>
      <p class="f4 lh-title mt3 mb0 font-serif">
        Building end-to-end data systems that hold up under scrutiny.
      </p>
      <p class="f5 lh-copy o-80 mt3 mb0 measure">
        I'm Jun — an applied data scientist based in San Diego, CA. I hold an
        M.S. in Applied Data Science from the University of San Diego, and bring
        20+ years of experience in regulated quality systems where the cost of
        bad data is real and every finding needs to withstand scrutiny.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Two-column layout -->
    <section class="flex-ns items-start-ns">
      <!-- Main/Left card -->
      <div class="w-100 w-60-ns pr0 pr4-ns mb4 mb0-ns">
        <section class="card pa4 pa5-ns">
          <h2 class="f3 fw6 mt0 mb3">What I do</h2>

          <p class="f5 lh-copy o-90 mt0">
            I build end-to-end data systems — from pipelines and feature
            engineering to deployed models and dashboards. My work sits at the
            intersection of analytics and engineering, with a focus on outputs
            that are reproducible, explainable, and defensible.
          </p>

          <p class="f5 lh-copy o-90">
            My regulated background means I approach data with a risk-based
            mindset. I don't just build models — I build systems designed to
            hold up under scrutiny.
          </p>

          <h3 class="f4 fw6 mt4 mb3">Focus areas</h3>
          <ul class="f5 lh-copy pl3 mt0 mb4">
            <li class="mb2">Predictive modeling and classification under class imbalance</li>
            <li class="mb2">Data engineering — pipelines, ETL, cloud-based workflows</li>
            <li class="mb2">NLP, sentiment analysis, and topic modeling</li>
            <li class="mb2">Reproducible EDA and open-source Python tooling</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="mt4">
            
            <a href="/projects"
              class="link br-pill ba b--white-20 ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib hover-bg-white-10"
            >
              View Projects →
            </a>
            
            <a href="/resources"
              class="link br-pill ba b--white-20 ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib hover-bg-white-10"
            >
              Resources →
            </a>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <!-- Side/Right card -->
      <aside class="w-100 w-40-ns mt0-ns">
        <section class="card pa4 pa5-ns mt0">
          <h2 class="f4 fw6 mt0 mb3">Toolkit</h2>

          <div>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">Python</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">R</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">SQL</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">scikit-learn</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">XGBoost</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">NLTK</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">AWS</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">Azure</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">MySQL</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">Tableau</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">Streamlit</span>
            <span class="ba b--white-10 br-pill ph3 pv2 f6 mr2 mb2 dib">Git</span>
          </div>

          <hr class="ba b--white-10 mv4" />

          <h2 class="f4 fw6 mt0 mb3">Outside of work</h2>
          <p class="f6 lh-copy o-80 mt0 mb0">
            When I'm not building data systems, I'm usually outdoors — kayaking,
            hiking, cycling, or on the tennis and pickleball courts. I also
            participate in charity rides when I can.
          </p>
        </section>
      </aside>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>